# DSL for defining Backbone.View hierarchies

It's not fully implemented yet!

## Specs

Specs are strings which can point to some JS object:

  * `module1/module2:obj1.obj2`
    points to `obj2` inside `obj1` in `module1/module2` AMD module.

  * `obj1.obj2`
    points to `obj2` inside `obj1` inside `window` object

## Wrap DOM with views

Wrap DOM with views, using standard tags:

    <div view="myapp/views:MyView" class="some-class"></div>

Attribute `view` should be a spec.

Passing parameters to views:

  * Parameter names are converted to camelCase, so `another-param` becomes
    `anotherParam`.

  * If parameter value starts with `this.` it then will be passed by reference
    and the reference will be equal to the one from the passed context.

## Value interpolation

Interpolate string values, DOM nodes and jQuery elements:

    <div>
      {{ somevalue }}
    </div>

## If blocks

    <div if="hasCounts">

    </div>

Element would be removed if `hasCounts()` or `hasCounts` evaluates to `false`.
